# Per-release extras files live in this directory.
#
# Convention: .github/release-extras/<tag>.md (e.g. v2026.5.6.0.md). If the
# file exists when the release workflow runs, its contents are appended below
# the auto-generated changelog slice with a `---` separator and an
# `## Additional notes` heading.
#
# Use only for content that genuinely cannot be captured in commit subjects:
# coordination notes for paired releases with the consumer overlays, migration
# instructions, links to a wiki page with long-form details. Anything that IS
# a code change should land as a conventional-commit subject and let the
# auto-generator pick it up.
#
# The same scrub gates (ASCII normalisation, voice + internal-only-vocabulary
# check) run on the composed body, so non-ASCII or marketing-puffery vocabulary
# in an extras file fails the workflow just as it would in a commit subject.
#
# See .github/RELEASE_WORKFLOW.md for the full policy.
